<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ900402-0030</DOCNO><DOCID>900402-0030.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Information International Inc.:   Litigation With Publisher   Over Software Is Settled</HL><DATE>04/02/90</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A8A</SO><CO>   IINT</CO><LP>   Information International Inc. said it settled certainlitigation with Morris Communications Corp. over computersoftware used for newspaper publishing and commercialprinting.   Under the settlements, which dealt with suits filed lastOctober in federal court in Georgia, Morris Communicationswithdrew demands for restitution of the $3 million purchaseprice of a software system bought from InformationInternational. For its part, Information International paidroyalty payments owed to Morris on separate software acquiredfrom Morris.</LP><TEXT>   Information International, based in Culver City, Calif.,makes computer software for the publishing business, amongothers. Closely held Morris Communications, based in Augusta,Ga., is a newspaper publishing concern.</TEXT></DOC>